post_text: We know our Abbott family has many questions regarding the reopening of school. Our leadership team as been working non-stop over the past few months coming up with a plan to reopen while keeping up with the ever changing mandates from the Federal & State Governements, TEA, UIL and local authorities. We sent out a survey last week allowing our parents to send us questions and concerns that they may have with reopening. We are so thankful for the questions that we received. Attached are the questions along with their answers. Please note that these are answers as of today. As madates and rules change, the answers may change also. If you still have questions or concerns after reading the Q&A, please contact our superintendent at eric.pustejovsky@abbottisd.org or our principal at jon.coker@abbottisd.org. It's a GREAT time to be an ABBOTT PANTHER! #PantherPride

Attached are the questions along with their answers. Please note that these are answers as of today. As madates and rules change, the answers may change also. If you still have questions or concerns after reading the Q&A, please contact our superintendent at eric.pustejovsky@abbottisd.org or our principal at jon.coker@abbottisd.org. It's a GREAT time to be an ABBOTT PANTHER! #PantherPride

post_text:
Please see the message from AYSA:

Unfortunately, after many hours of discussion and great effort by numerous volunteers, we have come up against countless reasons that are preventing us from hosting a football/cheer and volleyball season this year. Our youth and their health continues to be our number one priority, and we are grateful for your support and patience as we figure out these difficult and challenging decisions.

Our number one goal is to develop and teach our youth the amazing things that come from participating in team sports. As rules and regulations adjust, we will do our best to create opportunities to keep our kids loving to play. Until then, we hope you stay safe and healthy and we look forward to the time that we can all get together again!

post_text: Abbott ISD would like to welcome Laura Langdale. Mrs. Langdale is a special education teacher with experience from early childhood and throughout the transition process after students graduate. She has a Bachelor’s of Science degree from Tarleton State University with multiple certifications. She is a highly qualified teacher in all areas. Her mission is to motivate and introduce new and exciting teaching styles to individually meet her students needs. Therefore, achieving the ultimate goal of instilling a passion of lifelong learning in all of my students lives. She enjoys vegetable gardening, planting flowers, spoiling her 4-legged friends, an avid reader of all genres and anything outdoors. Mrs. Langdale loves to travel and has been to London, France, Switzerland, Italy and Greece. However, her favorite place on earth is the beach and a fishing pole. She will be on Amazon Prime if none of the above are available. Abbott ISD is excited to have Mrs. Langdale at Abbott ISD.

post_text:
We love and appreciate ESC 12!!!

To the teachers and parents of Central Texas,

We want to thank you!
For making sure learning doesn’t stop
For keeping our children and students at the top of your priority list
For your ongoing sacrifices and care for our children
For continuing to adapt and teach from your own home
For doing the best you can during a circumstance none of us could have prepared for

As providers of professional development for educators, we at Education Service Center Region 12 know that people are at the heart of education, and connection is the truest form of teaching…Your heroic efforts to continue to care, connect and teach have surrounded students with continuity and stability.

This Teacher Appreciation Week, we recognize the teachers-turned-caregivers and the caregivers-turned-teachers.

We’re all in this together!

STAAR testing update:

Grades 3-8: There will be no testing for this school year.

High school EOC testing:
Any student enrolled in an EOC tested subject (English I, English II, US History, Algebra I, and Biology) will not be required to take that EOC in high school.
Schools are waiting for clarification on how this will affect students who are retesting from previous STAAR administrations.
**UPDATE AS OF 7:40 pm on 1/19**
Clarification for STAAR EOC retesters will be required to continue to retest next school year.

DUAL CREDIT STUDENTS:

Hill College will resume classes on MONDAY, MARCH 23rd. Make sure that you log on to Schoology to continue your coursework. For the seniors, ENGL 1302 and MATH 1342, those classes will continue as well. You should get information for MATH 1342 on how to continue coursework and possibly watch videos. You need to check your Hill College email to get that information. For ENGL 1302, Mrs. Pustejovsky will be getting with Mrs. Blaha on how she would like to continue through the online platform. Be patient as we will be navigating through this with her. We will send you information about ENGL 1302 through your Abbott school email.

If you do not have access to internet to complete your coursework, please let Mrs. Pustejovsky know. I will work with you to make sure that you have access.

The safety of students and test center staff is our top priority. We have rescheduled the April 4 national test date across the U.S. in response to concerns about the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19).

All students registered for the April 4 test date will receive an email in the next few days informing them of the postponement and instructions for free rescheduling to June 13 or a future national test date.

More information: https://bit.ly/2QjSC3n

The safety of students and test center staff is our top priority. We have rescheduled the April 4 national test date across the U.S. in response to concerns about the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19).

All students registered for the April 4 test date will receive an email in the next few days informing them of the postponement and instructions for free rescheduling to June 13 or a future national test date.

More information: https://bit.ly/2QjSC3n

ACT.ORG
April 2020 National Exam COVID-19 - The ACT Test

post_text: The 4th and 5th graders voted yesterday for their favorite Bluebonnet Book. Each student had to read a minimum of 5 books from September thru December to be eligable to vote, chosing 1 book as their favorite. They then received a voters registration card to present on the voting day. The students cast their votes online in the library. Their votes were then sent to Austin, Texas to be tablated and submitted. We should find out in February which book is the Bluebonnet Winner. Great work to all who participated in this reading program! Thanks to our high school art classes for the awesome voter registration booth and posters!

REMINDER: The Creative Arts registration ends tonight!
Monday, January 27th will be check-in for your items. Doors open at 7:30 am and runs until 6 pm. We ask schools to please have their items there by 5 pm. The Creative Arts Division opens to the public at 1 pm on Wednesday, January 29th. Youth auction sign up is Wednesday, January 29th from 1 pm to 7 pm and Thursday, January 30th from 9 am to 2 pm. It is the responsibility of the exhibitor to see his/her name gets on the auction list. All Grand Champion, Reserve Champion and First Place items are eligible for auction. Participants may sell only one item. All items not in the auction must be picked up Thursday, January 30th from 4 pm to 7 pm or Friday, January 31st from 10 am to 4 pm. Please remember all no -auction items must be picked up by 4 pm on Friday, January 31st! Unfortunately we can not save items!
We look forward to seeing you at the Hill County Fair!

post_text:
📢 One week left to get your Creative Arts Division entries in for the Hill County Fair. Registration runs through Saturday, January 11th.
They have a few changes everyone will notice this year.
*Some Home Baked Foods classes have been combined and some are now a class of their own.
*Art, Photography and Craft divisions have size requirements and restrictions...please refer to the fair catalog for detailed information .
*Photography classes have been added to the Pre-K - First Grade age level.
*String art now has its own class in the Crafts Division.

They will use stickers again this year on placing items. Ribbons will be given when the items are checked out.
As always, if you have any questions feel free to call or email Lana Miller 245/205-2216 lanamiller548@gmail.com, Monika Rhea texasprincess78@yahoo.com or the HCF Creative Arts Division hcfcae@gmail.com.

Abbott FCA is extremely blessed with all the donations we have received for our Cook Children’s Hospital Fundraiser! Thank you to all of those who took the time to donate to this amazing cause.

Also, thank you to everyone who purchased FCA shirts so all the proceeds could go directly back into helping families this holiday season! We are very excited about delivering these items to the hospital in Fort Worth on Wednesday.

We would like to wish everyone a very Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year!
